How to run this project 

1. Download and extract the zip file.
2. Run 'npm install' in both frontend and backend folders to install the required dependencies 
3. Setup mongodb locally on your system, create a event-reminder database and in that create a collection named "reminders" to store the data.
4. Generate an app password for gmail from your google account security settings.
5. Create a .env file in your backend folder with the following details:
    PORT=5000
    MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/event-reminder  
    EMAIL_SERVICE=gmail
    EMAIL_USER= your@email.com
    EMAIL_PASS= the password generated from the 4th step
6. Open a terminal, cd to backend folder, run "node server.js", this will start the backend server.
7. Cd to frontend folder, run "npm start", this will run your app locally on browser.
